    <entry>
      <title>Big O Notation</title>
      <link href="/2021/08/10/Big-O-Notation/"/>
      <url>/2021/08/10/Big-O-Notation/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="1-Definition"><a href="#1-Definition" class="headerlink" title="1. Definition"></a>1. Definition</h1><p>Big O Notation is the language and metric use to <strong>describe the efficiency of algorithm</strong>.</p><h1 id="2-Purpose-to-use"><a href="#2-Purpose-to-use" class="headerlink" title="2. Purpose to use"></a>2. Purpose to use</h1><p>Software Engineer uses Big O Notation to <strong>estimate the efficiency</strong> of an algorithm by measuring 2 factor — <strong>time complexity</strong> and <strong>space complexity</strong>.</p><p>Software Engineer decide which algorithm to use to solve a problem by looking at the algorithm <strong>best case, average case, and worst case</strong> scenario.</p><h1 id="3-Types-of-Big-O-Notation"><a href="#3-Types-of-Big-O-Notation" class="headerlink" title="3. Types of Big O Notation"></a>3. Types of Big O Notation</h1><p><strong>Big O</strong><br>It is a complexity that is going to be <strong>less or equal</strong> to the worst case.</p><p><strong>Big - Ω (Big-Omega)</strong><br>It is a complexity that is going to be at <strong>less more than</strong> the best case.</p><p><strong>Big - Θ (Big-Theta)</strong><br>It is a complexity that is <strong>within bounds</strong> of the worst and best cases.</p><h1 id="4-Time-Complexity"><a href="#4-Time-Complexity" class="headerlink" title="4. Time Complexity"></a>4. Time Complexity</h1><div class="table-container"><table><thead><tr><th>Complexity</th><th>Name</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>O(1)</td><td>Constant</td><td>Accessing specific element in array</td></tr><tr><td>O(N)</td><td>Linear</td><td>Loop through array element</td></tr><tr><td>O(log N)</td><td>Logarithmic</td><td>Find an element in sorted array</td></tr><tr><td>O(N^2)</td><td>Quadratic</td><td>Loop through array element twice</td></tr><tr><td>O(2^N)</td><td>Exponential</td><td>Double recursion in Fibonacci</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><strong>Time Complexity (Fastest to Slowest)</strong><br>O(1) &lt; O(log N) &lt; O(n) &lt; O(N log N) &lt; O(n^2) &lt; O(n^3) &lt; O(2^N) &lt; O(N!)&lt; O(N^N)</p><p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jokerJun00/imagehost/master/d155tk2ttynxoehhz39k.jpeg"  width="55%" height="55%"></p><h1 id="5-Space-Complexity"><a href="#5-Space-Complexity" class="headerlink" title="5. Space Complexity"></a>5. Space Complexity</h1><div class="table-container"><table><thead><tr><th>Complexity</th><th>Name</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>O(1)</td><td>Constant</td><td>Bubble Sort</td></tr><tr><td>O(N)</td><td>Linear</td><td>Selection Sort</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h1 id="5-Logic"><a href="#5-Logic" class="headerlink" title="5. Logic"></a>5. Logic</h1><h3 id="5-1-Drop-Constants-and-Non-Dominant-Terms"><a href="#5-1-Drop-Constants-and-Non-Dominant-Terms" class="headerlink" title="5.1 Drop Constants and Non Dominant Terms"></a>5.1 Drop Constants and Non Dominant Terms</h3><ol><li>Drop Constant<ul><li>O(2N) -&gt; o(N)</li></ul></li><li>Drop Non Dominant Terms<ul><li>O(N^2 + N) -&gt; O(N^2)</li></ul></li></ol><p><strong>Reason</strong></p><ol><li>Different computers with different architectures have <strong>different constant factors</strong></li><li>There is omit constants and non dominant terms only create <strong>sligt difference</strong> but faster to let software engineer determine which algorithm is faster.</li></ol><h3 id="5-2-Add-vs-Multiple-Complexity"><a href="#5-2-Add-vs-Multiple-Complexity" class="headerlink" title="5.2 Add vs Multiple Complexity"></a>5.2 Add vs Multiple Complexity</h3><p>Depends on the code arrangement, addition or multiplication of complexity will happend</p><p><strong>Add complexity</strong><br>Big O notation = O(A) + O(B) = <strong>O(A + B)</strong><br><strong>Multiply complexity</strong><br>Big O notation = O(A) * O(B) = <strong>O(AB)</strong></p><p><strong>Example</strong><br>Big O Notation = O(N + N) = O(2N) = O(N) <strong>(Drop constant)</strong><br><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span> (a = <span class="hljs-number">0</span>; arrayA.length; a++) &#123;<br>    System.out.println(arrayA[a]);<br>&#125;<br><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span> (b = <span class="hljs-number">0</span>; arrayB.length; b++) &#123;<br>    System.out.println(arrayB[b]);<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><p>Big O Notation = O(N * N) = O(N^2)<br><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span> (a = <span class="hljs-number">0</span>; arrayA.length; a++) &#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-keyword">for</span> (b = <span class="hljs-number">0</span>; arrayB.length; b++) &#123;<br>    System.out.println(arrayA[a] + arrayB[b]);<br>    &#125;<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p>]]></content>
      
      
