      <title>Interview Question: Recursion </title>
      <link href="/2021/08/08/Recursion-Interview-Question/"/>
      <url>/2021/08/08/Recursion-Interview-Question/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Question-1"><a href="#Question-1" class="headerlink" title="Question 1"></a>Question 1</h1><hr><p>How to find the sum of digits of a positive integer number using recursion?</p><p><strong>Example</strong><br>Input: 112<br>Output: 4<br>Input: 38<br>Output: 11<br>Input: 12<br>Output: 3<br>Input: 10<br>Output: 1</p><h4 id="Explaination"><a href="#Explaination" class="headerlink" title="Explaination"></a>Explaination</h4><p>Solution need to <strong>add up all the digit</strong> from the given input.</p><h4 id="Solution"><a href="#Solution" class="headerlink" title="Solution"></a>Solution</h4><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">Main</span> </span>&#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">main</span><span class="hljs-params">(String[] args)</span></span>&#123;<br>        Main main = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> Main();<br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> result = main.sumOfDigit(<span class="hljs-number">4</span>);<br>        System.out.println(result);<br>    &#125;<br><br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> <span class="hljs-title">sumOfDigit</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> n)</span></span>&#123;<br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Base case: n = 0, Unintentional case: n &lt; 0</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (n == <span class="hljs-number">0</span>)&#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-number">0</span>;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Recursive case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> n%<span class="hljs-number">10</span> + sumOfDigit(n/<span class="hljs-number">10</span>);<br>    &#125;<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id="Question-2"><a href="#Question-2" class="headerlink" title="Question 2"></a>Question 2</h1><hr><p>How to calculate power of a number using recursion?</p><p>Input: base = 2, exponent = 2<br>Output: 4<br>Input: base = 2, exponent = 1<br>Output: 2<br>Input: base = 5, exponent = 3<br>Output: 125</p><h4 id="Explaination-1"><a href="#Explaination-1" class="headerlink" title="Explaination"></a>Explaination</h4><p>Solution need to calculate the final value from inputs (base number and its exponents).<br><code>x^a * x^b = X^(a+b)</code></p><p>Thus, in the recursive expression<br><code>x^n = x * x^(n-1)</code></p><h4 id="Solution-1"><a href="#Solution-1" class="headerlink" title="Solution"></a>Solution</h4><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">Main</span> </span>&#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">main</span><span class="hljs-params">(String[] args)</span></span>&#123;<br>        Main main = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> Main();<br>    &#125;<br><br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> <span class="hljs-title">power</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> base, <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> exp)</span> </span>&#123;<br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Unintentional case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (exp &lt; <span class="hljs-number">0</span>) &#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Base case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (exp == <span class="hljs-number">0</span>) &#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-number">1</span>;<br>        &#125;<br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (exp == <span class="hljs-number">1</span>)&#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> base;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Recursive case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> base * power(base, exp-<span class="hljs-number">1</span>);<br>    &#125;<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id="Question-3"><a href="#Question-3" class="headerlink" title="Question 3"></a>Question 3</h1><hr><p>How to find GCD (Greatest Common Divisor) of two numbers using recursion?</p><p>Input: 8, 12<br>Output: 4</p><h4 id="Explanation"><a href="#Explanation" class="headerlink" title="Explanation"></a>Explanation</h4><p><strong>GCD</strong><br>The largest positive integer that divides the numebrs without a remainder.</p><p>Example<br>GCD for 8 and 12<br>gcd(8, 12) = 4</p><p>8 = 2<em>2</em>2<br>12 = 2<em>2</em>3</p><p><strong>Euclidean algorithm</strong></p><ol><li>Divide larger number with smaller number(as divisor).</li><li>Use the previous divisor divide with the remainder. </li><li>Repeat step 2.</li></ol><p>By using Euclidean algorithm, we can simplify the steps to calculate GCD.</p><h4 id="Solution-2"><a href="#Solution-2" class="headerlink" title="Solution"></a>Solution</h4><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">Main</span>()</span>&#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">main</span><span class="hljs-params">(String[] args)</span></span>&#123;<br>        Main main = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> Main();<br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> result = main.gcd(-<span class="hljs-number">8</span>, <span class="hljs-number">4</span>);<br>        System.out.println(result);<br>    &#125;<br><br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> <span class="hljs-title">gcd</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> a, <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> b)</span></span>&#123;<br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Unintentional Case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (a &lt; <span class="hljs-number">0</span> || b &lt; <span class="hljs-number">0</span>) &#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Base Case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (b == <span class="hljs-number">0</span>)&#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> a;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Recursive case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> gcd(b, a%b);<br>    &#125;<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id="Question-4"><a href="#Question-4" class="headerlink" title="Question 4"></a>Question 4</h1><hr><p>How to convert a number from Decimal to Binary using recursion<br>Input: 13<br>Output: 1101<br>Input: 20<br>Output: 10100</p><h4 id="Explanation-1"><a href="#Explanation-1" class="headerlink" title="Explanation"></a>Explanation</h4><p>Steps</p><ol><li>Divide number by 2</li><li>Get the integer quotient for the next iteration</li><li>Get the remainder for the binary digit</li><li>Repeat steps 1 to 3 until quotient = 0.</li></ol><p><strong>Example</strong></p><div class="table-container"><table><thead><tr><th>Division by 2</th><th>Quotient</th><th>Remainder</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>13/2</td><td>6</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>6/2</td><td>3</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>3/2</td><td>1</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>1/2</td><td>0</td><td>1</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Remainder: 1 1 0 1</p><p>To get the int from recursion, we need to modify remainders when we return the remainders. </p><p><strong>Example</strong></p><ol><li>1 * 10 + 1 = 11</li><li>11 * 10 + 0 = 110</li><li>110 * 10 + 1 = 1101</li></ol><p>Thus, the formula will be <code>f(n) = n mod 2 + 10 * f(n/2)</code>.<br>mod = modulus</p><h4 id="Solution-3"><a href="#Solution-3" class="headerlink" title="Solution"></a>Solution</h4><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">Main</span>()</span>&#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">main</span><span class="hljs-params">(String[] args)</span></span>&#123;<br>        Main main = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> Main();<br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> result = main.decimalToBinary(<span class="hljs-number">13</span>);<br>        System.out.println(result);<br>    &#125;<br><br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> <span class="hljs-title">decimalToBinary</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> n)</span> </span>&#123;<br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Unintentinal case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (n &lt; <span class="hljs-number">0</span>)&#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Base case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (n == <span class="hljs-number">0</span>) &#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> n;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Recursive case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> n%<span class="hljs-number">2</span> + decimalToBinary(n/<span class="hljs-number">2</span>);<br>    &#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      
      
