      <title>Algorithm: Recursion</title>
      <link href="/2021/08/08/Recursion/"/>
      <url>/2021/08/08/Recursion/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="1-Definition"><a href="#1-Definition" class="headerlink" title="1.Definition"></a>1.Definition</h1><p>Recusion is a way of solving problem by having a function <strong>calling itself</strong></p><h1 id="2-Properties"><a href="#2-Properties" class="headerlink" title="2. Properties"></a>2. Properties</h1><ul><li>Performing the same operation multiple times <strong>with different inputs</strong>.</li><li>Try <strong>smaller inputs</strong> in every steps to make the problem smaller.</li><li>Use <strong>base condition</strong> to <strong>stop recursion</strong>, otherwise infinite loop will occur.</li></ul><h1 id="3-Purpose-to-use"><a href="#3-Purpose-to-use" class="headerlink" title="3. Purpose to use"></a>3. Purpose to use</h1><ul><li>To <strong>divine problem</strong> into similar sub problem.</li><li><strong>n th</strong> type problem. (Design an algorithm to compute nth…, Write code to list the n…)</li><li>Computing problem. (Implement a method to compute all)</li><li>Use in data structure. (<strong>tree &amp; graphs</strong>) </li><li>Use in many algorithm. (<strong>divide and conquer, greedy algorithm, dynamic programming</strong>)</li></ul><h1 id="4-When"><a href="#4-When" class="headerlink" title="4. When"></a>4. When</h1><hr><h3 id="4-1-When-to-use"><a href="#4-1-When-to-use" class="headerlink" title="4.1 When to use"></a>4.1 When to use</h3><ul><li>Problem can <strong>easily breakdown</strong> into sub problems</li><li>Problem is <strong>fine with extra</strong> overhead(time and space)</li><li>We <strong>need a quick working solution</strong> instead of efficient one</li><li><strong>Travese</strong> a tree</li><li>Use <strong>memoization</strong> in recursion (Time complexity can be redo)</li></ul><h3 id="4-2-When-to-avoid"><a href="#4-2-When-to-avoid" class="headerlink" title="4.2 When to avoid"></a>4.2 When to avoid</h3><ul><li>Time and space complexity matters for us</li><li>Application <strong>using embedded memory</strong>(mobile application)</li></ul><h1 id="5-Logic"><a href="#5-Logic" class="headerlink" title="5. Logic"></a>5. Logic</h1><hr><h3 id="5-1-Condition"><a href="#5-1-Condition" class="headerlink" title="5.1 Condition"></a>5.1 Condition</h3><ol><li>Base condition (Exit from infinite loop)</li><li>A method to calls it self</li></ol><p><strong>Pseudocode</strong><br><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> string <span class="hljs-title">recursionMethod</span><span class="hljs-params">(String[] parameters)</span> </span>&#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-comment">// Base condition</span><br>    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (exit from condition satisfied) &#123;<br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> some value;<br>    &#125; <br><br>    <span class="hljs-comment">// recall itself</span><br>    recursionMethod(modified parameters);<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p><h3 id="5-2-Concept"><a href="#5-2-Concept" class="headerlink" title="5.2 Concept"></a>5.2 Concept</h3><ul><li>Method will <strong>saves in stack memory</strong> if it call a function and <strong>waiting</strong> for called method to execute first.</li><li>Called method will <strong>stack on top</strong> of the caling method in stack memory and execute. </li><li>Once the called method finish execute, called method will <strong>remove from stack memory</strong> and calling method will <strong>continue its execution</strong>. </li><li>Stack memory will only execute the <strong>top most method</strong> first based on its <strong>FILO (First in Last out)</strong> property.</li></ul><p><strong>Example</strong><br><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jokerJun00/imagehost/master/Recursion_Stack2.png"  width="55%" height="55%"></p><figure class="highlight java"><figcaption><span>Example code</span></figcaption><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> string <span class="hljs-title">firstMethod</span><span class="hljs-params">()</span> </span>&#123;<br>    secondMethod();<br>    System.out.println(<span class="hljs-string">&quot;I am the first method&quot;</span>);<br>&#125;<br><br><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> string <span class="hljs-title">secondMethod</span><span class="hljs-params">()</span> </span>&#123;<br>    thirdMethod();<br>    System.out.println(<span class="hljs-string">&quot;I am the second method&quot;</span>);<br>&#125;<br><br><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> string <span class="hljs-title">thirdMethod</span><span class="hljs-params">()</span> </span>&#123;<br>    fourthMethod();<br>    System.out.println(<span class="hljs-string">&quot;I am the third method&quot;</span>);<br>&#125;<br><br><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> string <span class="hljs-title">fourthMethod</span><span class="hljs-params">()</span> </span>&#123;<br>    System.out.println(<span class="hljs-string">&quot;I am the fourth method&quot;</span>);<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><figure class="highlight shell"><figcaption><span>Output</span></figcaption><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs Shell">I am the fourth method<br>I am the third method<br>I am the second method<br>I am the first method<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id="6-Recursion-vs-Iteration"><a href="#6-Recursion-vs-Iteration" class="headerlink" title="6. Recursion vs Iteration"></a>6. Recursion vs Iteration</h1><div class="table-container"><table><thead><tr><th>Points</th><th>Recursion</th><th>Iteration</th><th>Explanation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Space efficiency</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td><td>No stack memory in iteration</td></tr><tr><td>Time efficiency</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td><td>Recursion need more time to <strong>pop and push</strong> elements in stack memory</td></tr><tr><td>Coding difficulty</td><td>Easier</td><td>Harder</td><td>Use recursion when the problem can divide to sub problem</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h1 id="7-3-steps-to-write-Recursion"><a href="#7-3-steps-to-write-Recursion" class="headerlink" title="7. 3 steps to write Recursion"></a>7. 3 steps to write Recursion</h1><ol><li>Recursive case</li><li>Base case</li><li>Unintentional case = the constraint (<strong>return -1</strong> to reject the input case)</li></ol><p><strong>Fibonacci numbers</strong><br><figure class="highlight java"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">Main</span> </span>&#123;<br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">main</span><span class="hljs-params">(String[] args)</span></span>&#123;<br>        Main recursion = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> Main();<br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">var</span> rec = recursion. fibonacci(<span class="hljs-number">3</span>);<br>        System.out.println(rec);<br>    &#125;<br><br>    <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">int</span>  <span class="hljs-title">fibonacci</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">int</span> n)</span> </span>&#123;<br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Unintentional case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (n &lt; <span class="hljs-number">0</span>) &#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> -<span class="hljs-number">1</span>;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Base case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (n == <span class="hljs-number">0</span> || n == <span class="hljs-number">1</span>)&#123;<br>            <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> n;<br>        &#125;<br><br>        <span class="hljs-comment">// Recursive case</span><br>        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> fibonacci(n-<span class="hljs-number">1</span>) + fibonacci(n-<span class="hljs-number">2</span>)<br>    &#125;<br>&#125;<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p>]]></content>
      
      
      <categories>
          
          <category> Algorihtm </category>
          
